text:
Long John Silveira, retired porn legend, stares at his dingy wall, adorned with crooked awards (Wide Load 1975, The Last Cupper 1988). He simply exists now - loveless, hopeless, utterly devoid of the energy that once characterized him. 

The landline rings. "Yeah?" "Hi. May I speak with John Silveira?" "Uh, yeah, that's me." "My grandmother just passed. You...you two worked together. I'd like to meet, if that's okay." 

And so it begins. Relive the highs and lows of Long John Silveira. Where has he been, and where will he go? A tale of freedom, excess, tragedy, and maybe, just maybe, purpose. 

Danny Trejo is John Silveira.
